sca.check.remediation: - IF - A user profile exists run the following commands to ensure automatic mounting is disabled: # gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount false # gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount-open false Note: - gsettings commands in this section MUST be done from a command window on a graphical desktop or an error will be returned. - The system must be restarted after all gsettings configurations have been set in order for CIS-CAT Assessor to appropriately assess. - OR/IF - A user profile does not exist: 1. Create a file /etc/dconf/db/local.d/00-media-automount with following content: [org/gnome/desktop/media-handling] automount=false automount-open=false 2. After creating the file, apply the changes using below command : # dconf update Note: Users must log out and back in again before the system-wide settings take effect.
