sca.check.rationale: If there is no need to mount directories and file systems to Windows systems, then this service should be deleted to reduce the potential attack surface.
sca.check.remediation: Run the following commands to stop smbd.service and remove samba package: # systemctl stop smbd.service # apt purge samba - OR - - IF - the samba package is required as a dependency: Run the following commands to stop and mask the smbd.service: # systemctl stop smbd.service # systemctl mask smbd.service.
